x4freetext: -(N,N G) REACTIONS IN 23-V-51 AND 39-Y-89.-
AWRE 6 MV VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR.
T(P,N)-REACTION, TRITIUM GAS TARGET WITH A
3.48 MG/CM2 MO ENTRANCE FOIL FILLED TO 760 TORR GAS
PRESSURE.
THE INCIDENT NEUTRON ENERGIES 0.3 TO 4 MEV,
THE ENERGY SPREAD OF THE NEUTRON INCIDENT ON THE
SCATTERER WAS APPROXIMATELY 120 KEV AT 0.3 MEV
INCIDENT ENERGY AND 40 KEV AT 4.0 MEV.
TIME OF FLIGHT,
.RING GEOMETRY.
A 20 CC COAXIALLY DRIFTED GE(LI) DETECTOR.
THE SYSTEM SHOWED A FULL ENERGY PEAK TO COMPTON EDGE
RATIO OF OVER 9 TO 1 FOR CS-137 (662 KEV) G-RAYS AND
ENERGY RESOLUTION (FWHM) OF ABOUT 5 KEV.
A PAIR OF LONG COUNTERS FOR THE N-MONITOR.
GAMMA-RAYS FROM SCATTERER WERE EMITTED BETWEEN 83 AND
118 DEG TO THE MEAN INCIDENT NEUTRON DIRECTION. THUS
MEAN ANGLE WAS 100 DEG.
HAUSER-FESHBACH THEORY MODIFIED FOR LEVEL
WIDTH FLUCTUATION.
2 SEPARATE SERIES OF EXPERIMENTS, SERIES I IN THE
ENERGY RANGE 0.3 TO 3.1 MEV, AND SERIES II 2.2 TO 4.0
MEV IN 0.2 MEV STEPS HAVE BEEN PERFORMED.
THE EXPERIMENTS WERE NOT INTENDED TO YIELD ABSOLUTE
VALUES FOR THE 100 DEG. DIFFERENTIAL X-SECT. BY
THEMSELVES BUT RELATIVE GAMMA-RAY PRODUCTION
FUNCTIONS WHICH COULD BE RENORMALIZED TO AN ABSOLUTE
SCALE BY COMPARING THE G-RAY YIELD FROM A LEVEL WITH
THE ABSOLUTE VALUE FOR THE INELASTIC X-SECT. TO THIS
LEVEL AS FOUND BY TOYLE (NP/A,117,657(68) AND
CORRECTIONS FOR ABSORPTION OF THE GAMMA-RAYS IN THE
SCATTERER AND MULTIPLE INELASTIC SCATTERING EFFECTS.
THE MAGGIE PROGRAM (PARKER+, NIM 30(1964)77) WAS USED
THE ERRORS ON THE CROSS SECTIONS ARE ONE STANDARD
DEVIATION AND ARE COMBINATION OF THE RELATIVE ERROR
AND ERRORS DUE TO ABSOLUTE NORMALISATION.

x4freetext: AT 100 DEG.
NATURAL V (V-50 0.24 PERC.,V-51 99.76 PERC.) IN
POWDER FORM, 99.5 PERC. PURE, PACKED INTO
TOROIDAL PERSPEX CONTAINER OF RECTANGULAR CROSS-
SECTION. O.D. = 15.24 CM, I.D. = 9.84 CM, DEPTH = 3.81
CM, WALL THICKNESS = 0.16 CM.
TO THE 1.6101 MEV BY TOWLE, NUCL.PHYS.A117(1968)657,
.FULL ENERGY PEAK DETECTION EFFICENCY OF GE(LI)
SPECTROMETER WAS DETERMINED BY THE 88-RA-226 SOURCE,
AND UP TO ABOUT 3.6 MEV BY A STRONG SOURCE OF CO-56.
.SERIES I RESULTS WERE NORMALISED SERIES II VIA THE
LONG COUNTER.  SEE MAINCOMMENT.
GAMMAS.
AS EXPLAINED IN MAIN COMMENT TWO SERIES OF
EXPERIMENTS WERE PERFORMED. THE RESULTS GIVEN BELOW
WERE OBTAINED BY MERGING THOSE OF THE TWO SERIES.
DATA FROM TABLES 1A AND 1B, PAG.23, AND 1C, PAG. 24
OF THE PUBLICATION.
